Yeah, I'm just gonna fix those autocard tags. Combos ridiculously with [Thornbite Staff](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Thornbite Staff) (it just destroys all tapped creatures). Also combos well with [Urabrask the Hidden](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Urabrask the Hidden) (@colvinced there's no comma, unlike [", the"](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=", the") dragons.  

Combos well with [Repel the Darkness](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Repel the Darkness), new card [Dispatch](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Dispatch), one half of [Blinding Beam](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Blinding Beam), [all](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?multiverseid=233045) [five](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?multiverseid=205219) [versions](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?multiverseid=83162) [of](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?multiverseid=222708) [Blinding Mage](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Blinding Mage). I see UBW control.  

@Henrietta: Tapping Royal Assassin is irrelevant, because the cost is immediate and doesn't use the stack. They can kill Royal Assassin, but his ability is still on the stack and will still resolve.

